message: "Locally, Chronister said, Hillsborough County Commissioner Kimberly Overman is working with the Sheriff's Office on a county ordinance that would target rental properties, including apartments, houses and hotels with hourly rates, that facilitate prostitution that exploits victims of human trafficking."

data.description: Monday's human trafficking summit, the first ever organized by the Greater Tampa Chamber of Commerce, attracted nearly 200 people.
data.title: In fight against sex and labor trafficking, Tampa chamber works to enlist businesses
